SEND STREAMER A TEXT - FEATURE SUMMARY
==============================================================================

==============================================================================
ūüß† PURPOSE
==============================================================================
This private delivery action takes a channel-point redemption message, adds the
redeemer‚Äôs username, and sends the result through an email-to-SMS gateway.

After a successful SMTP send it waits briefly and optionally plays a local sound.
Both delivery failures and successful sends remain silent in Twitch chat.

==============================================================================
ūüĒĄ SYSTEM FLOW
==============================================================================
STEP 1: MESSAGE INPUT
--------------------------------
- Reads rawInput from the redemption and exits when no message was supplied.

STEP 2: SENDER SIGNATURE
--------------------------------
- Appends the redeeming viewer‚Äôs username to the outgoing message body.

STEP 3: SMTP DELIVERY
--------------------------------
- Connects to Gmail SMTP on port 587 with SSL.
- Sends the message to the configured carrier gateway address without a subject.

STEP 4: LOCAL CONFIRMATION
--------------------------------
- Waits four seconds after a successful send and plays the configured sound file.

STEP 5: SILENT FAILURE
--------------------------------
- Catches delivery errors without posting a public error message.

==============================================================================
ūüď¶ VARIABLE REFERENCE
==============================================================================
rawInput
--------------------------------
Viewer-supplied message text from the redemption.

user
--------------------------------
Redeemer username appended to the outgoing message.

fiGatewayAddress
--------------------------------
Private email-to-SMS destination for the streamer‚Äôs phone.

YOUR_EMAIL@example.com
--------------------------------
Placeholder for the SMTP sending account.

YOUR_APP_PASSWORD
--------------------------------
Placeholder for an email-provider app password.

C:\PATH\TO\YOUR\SOUND_FILE.mp3
--------------------------------
Placeholder local sound path used after successful delivery.

==============================================================================
ūüé® USER CUSTOMIZATION
==============================================================================
SMS GATEWAY
--------------------------------
- Replace YOUR_PHONE_NUMBER@YOUR_CARRIER_GATEWAY with the private gateway address supplied by the mobile carrier.
- Verify that the carrier still supports email-to-SMS delivery.

EMAIL CREDENTIALS
--------------------------------
- Replace both YOUR_EMAIL@example.com values with the sending email account.
- Replace YOUR_APP_PASSWORD with an app-specific password, never the account‚Äôs normal password.

CONFIRMATION SOUND
--------------------------------
- Replace C:\PATH\TO\YOUR\SOUND_FILE.mp3 with an existing local audio file.
- Adjust 0.5f to change playback volume or remove the PlaySound line.

REDEMPTION ACCESS
--------------------------------
- Restrict the reward to trusted viewers or apply moderation limits appropriate for private text delivery.

ERROR VISIBILITY
--------------------------------
- Add CPH.LogError inside catch when silent SMTP failures are too difficult to diagnose.

==============================================================================
ūüď° EMAIL-TO-SMS CARRIER REFERENCE
==============================================================================
CURRENT STATUS ‚ÄĒ VERIFY BEFORE ENTERING PRIVATE INFORMATION
--------------------------------
Carrier gateways are legacy services and can be changed, filtered, delayed, or
retired without notice. Test delivery with a private account before relying on it.

T-MOBILE
--------------------------------
- SMS format: 10digitnumber@tmomail.net
- T-Mobile currently documents this gateway for SMS email delivery.
- Use plain-text email; HTML content is not supported by the gateway.

VERIZON
--------------------------------
- Legacy SMS format: 10digitnumber@vtext.com
- Legacy MMS format: 10digitnumber@vzwpix.com
- Verizon is shutting down Vtext/VZWPix, with completion expected by March 31, 2027.
- Access may stop earlier for some senders, so do not treat it as a permanent option.

AT&T
--------------------------------
- The former txt.att.net and mms.att.net gateways are no longer supported.
- AT&T ended email-to-text and text-to-email service on June 17, 2025.
- Do not configure this script with an AT&T gateway address.

OTHER CARRIERS AND MVNOS
--------------------------------
- Ask the carrier whether it currently supports consumer email-to-SMS.
- Do not assume a reseller or MVNO uses the gateway of its underlying network.
- Confirm the exact address format, message limits, spam filtering, and opt-in rules.

DELIVERY LIMITATIONS
--------------------------------
- Email-to-SMS is not guaranteed, encrypted, or suitable for emergencies.
- Messages may be delayed, truncated, blocked as automated traffic, or silently dropped.
- Some carriers may not support gateways. Check with your carrier for more info!

==============================================================================
ūüĒź DATA SAFETY
==============================================================================
WHY THIS SCRIPT IS HIGH RISK
--------------------------------
- The gateway address commonly contains the streamer‚Äôs real phone number. Publishing it can expose a direct contact destination and may enable harassment, spam, stalking, or unwanted account-recovery attempts.
- The sender email identifies a real account that can be targeted with phishing, credential-stuffing, impersonation, or password-reset attacks.
- An exposed app password can grant another person access to send mail through the account and may remain usable even when the normal account password is changed.
- The local sound-file path can reveal the Windows username, folder structure, installed software, or other identifying details about the computer.
- Viewer-supplied text may itself contain private or abusive content. Email-to-SMS delivery is not a secure channel and should never be treated as encrypted messaging.

NEVER SHARE THESE ITEMS
--------------------------------
- Never upload a completed .cs file, Streamer.bot export, screenshot, screen recording, log, GitHub repository, Discord attachment, Pastebin entry, or support ticket that contains real contact or credential values.
- Never show the real gateway address, sender email, app password, SMTP credential object, or identifying local file path‚ÄĒeven briefly during a livestream or tutorial.
- Never use the email account‚Äôs normal sign-in password in this script. Only use a revocable app-specific password when the provider supports one.
- Do not copy SMTP errors into a public post until you have checked that the error text does not echo an email address, destination, message body, token, or server response containing private information.

BEFORE SHARING OR SELLING THIS TEMPLATE
--------------------------------
- Replace the phone gateway with YOUR_PHONE_NUMBER@YOUR_CARRIER_GATEWAY.
- Replace every sender address with YOUR_EMAIL@example.com and every app password with YOUR_APP_PASSWORD.
- Replace the sound path with C:\PATH\TO\YOUR\SOUND_FILE.mp3 and remove any computer username from comments or screenshots.
- Search the entire file and export for @, smtp, password, credential, phone-number patterns, Windows user-folder paths, drive-letter paths, and any real usernames before publishing.
- Open the final ZIP or export itself and inspect the packaged copy. Sanitizing only the source file is not enough if an older unsanitized copy remains inside the archive.
- Test the public template with placeholders or a separate test account rather than restoring real credentials before distribution.

SAFER CONFIGURATION PRACTICES
--------------------------------
- Store credentials in protected Streamer.bot variables, environment variables, or a dedicated secret manager instead of hardcoding them when possible.
- Use a separate sending account with the minimum access needed, enable multi-factor authentication, and create a unique app password only for this automation.
- Restrict the redemption and action to trusted users, apply rate limits, and avoid allowing unmoderated text to be forwarded directly to a private phone.
- Keep private diagnostic logs local, limit who can read the action, and do not sync credential-bearing files to public cloud folders or repositories.

IF INFORMATION IS ACCIDENTALLY EXPOSED
--------------------------------
- Immediately revoke the exposed app password in the email provider‚Äôs security settings and create a new one only after the public copy has been removed.
- If the normal email password was ever used, change it immediately, sign out other sessions, review recent account activity, and confirm multi-factor authentication is enabled.
- Delete or replace the exposed file everywhere it was posted, including mirrors, message attachments, repository history, releases, and cached downloadable archives.
- Treat an exposed phone gateway as an exposed phone number. Prepare for spam, block abusive senders, and contact the mobile carrier if harassment or account-security concerns begin.
- Assume anything posted publicly may have been copied even after deletion; rotating credentials is required and removing the post alone is not sufficient.

